The paper focuses on machine learning-based data rate prediction for mobile and vehicular networks, which falls under the category of computer networks and communications (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of cooperative prediction approaches, which involves knowledge from both the client and network domains, indicating a potential overlap with machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also mentions the use of Software Defined Radio (SDR) for network monitoring, which could be classified under multimedia (cs.MM) or cryptography and security (cs.CR) depending on the specific application.
